Ingredients Dry 3 c All purpose flour 1/4 c Sugar 1 1/2 tsp salt 1 tbsp baking powder 1 1/2 tsp baking soda Wet 2 1/4 c milk 1/4 c vegetable oil 1 tbsp vanilla extract 1/4 c apple cider vinegar 1 (optional) 1 egg, reduce milk by 1/4 cup if adding egg Whipped salted butter 1 stick of salted butter at room temperature 1 tbsp cold water Directions Pancakes Mix dry and wet in separate bowls.2 Combine the dry and wet. Do not overmix when combining. Fold only 20-25 times until combined (Lumps are ok) 3 Cook pancakes on medium high heat Watch for bubbles start to form before flipping Whipped salted butter Add a teaspoon to tablespoon of cold water to softened butter Whip until light and airy Footnotes It&rsquo;s going to seem like a lot of apple cider vinegar, and you&rsquo;re going to smell it and wonder, &ldquo;What am I doing?&rdquo; But it&rsquo;s ok. It&rsquo;s going to taste great. Trust the process.&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
While in separate bowls, they can be mixed thoroughly.&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
Don&rsquo;t overmix! Thick batter = big bubbles = fluffy Pancakes&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
